##✋ Signify - Sign Language Translator

A web application that helps bridge the communication gap between sign language users and people who do not know LSM (Mexican Sign Language).



##🎯 Project Objective

This project was developed as part of an educational program for students interested in technology and coding. The main goals are:

* Learn programming: Develop practical coding skills
* Teamwork: Collaborate to solve a real-world problem
* Social impact: Create an inclusive communication tool



##🚀 Features

🤲 LSM to Text Translator

* Hand gesture detection using MediaPipe
* Recognition of basic letters (A–E) based on finger positions
* Real-time camera interaction in the browser
* Word formation letter by letter

##🎤 Voice to Text

* Speech recognition using Web Speech API
* Spanish language support
* Real-time transcription

##🎨 User Interface

* Responsive design with simple layout
* Real-time visual feedback
* User-friendly interaction



##🛠️ Technology

Backend

* Flask – Python web framework
* OpenCV – Image processing
* MediaPipe – Hand landmark detection
* NumPy – Numerical operations

Frontend

* HTML5 / CSS3
* JavaScript
* Web Speech API



