##📖 How to Use

LSM to Text Mode

1. Allow camera access when prompted
2. Position your hand in front of the camera
3. Use gestures based on finger positions:
    * A: 0 fingers
    * B: 1 finger
    * C: 2 fingers
    * D: 3 fingers
    * E: 4 fingers
4. The detected letter will appear automatically
5. Continue forming words



Voice to Text Mode

1. Click “Start Dictation”
2. Allow microphone access
3. Speak clearly in Spanish
4. Text will appear in real time
5. Click “Stop Dictation” when finished



##🔄 Real-Time Processing Approach

Instead of using OpenCV windows (cv2.imshow), this project processes camera input directly in the browser:

* The frontend captures frames from the webcam
* Frames are sent periodically to the Flask backend
* MediaPipe processes each frame
* Results are returned and displayed on the same page

This allows the system to run entirely inside a web interface without opening external windows.



##⏱️ Real-Time Behavior

The system simulates real-time detection by sending frames at short intervals (approximately every 0.5 seconds).
This approach provides a responsive experience while keeping the implementation simple and efficient.



